laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated and fluid filled measuring up to 10 mm in maximal dimension. There is minimal periappendiceal fat stranding, but no abscess collection. There is no evidence of perforation or free air. The lung bases are clear. The liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, bilateral adrenal glands, and kidneys are normal. The kidneys are homogeneously enhancing and excreting urine without evidence of stones. There is no retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy. The systemic arterial, systemic venous and portal venous system of the abdomen and pelvis are normal. The esophagus, stomach, and small bowel are normal. The remainder of the colon and rectum are normal. The urinary bladder is normal. The ovaries are normal. There is no pelvic lymphadenopathy. There is mild S-shaped scoliosis of the lumbar spine, possibly positional. There are no suspicious lytic or sclerotic bony lesions.
